                  </hi>. I am the wife of Edward Harper, a greengrocer, of the Back-road, Kingsland. On 16th Oct., about twelve o'clock, the pri<lb></lb>soner came to my stall—he said, "Is this Ned Harper's stall?"—I said, "Yes"—he said my husband had sent him for the barrow—I gave him the key to go and take it—I afterwards saw him at the station.</p>
